{{Sangam literature}}
'''Kārikkannanār''', known in full as '''Kāviripoompattinathu Kārikkannanār''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: காவிரிப்பூம்பட்டினத்துக் காரிக்கண்ணனார்), was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom 10 verses of the Sangam literature have been attributed, including verse 28 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages = 42–43 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Hailing from Kaveri Poompattinam, Kaari Kannanar was a trader by occupation and has sung in praise of kings Chola Kura Palli Thunjiya Perunthirumavalavan, Pandiyan Ilavanthigai Palli Thunjiya Nanmaran, Pandiyan Velliyambalatthu Thunjiya Peruvaludhi, Aai Aandiran, and Pittan Kottran.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = அகநானூறு, புறநானூறு [Agananuru, Purananuru] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 3 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 393, 405–406 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> He compared the [[Chola dynasty|Chola]] and [[Pandya dynasty|Pandiya]] rulers with [[Lord Vishnu]] and [[Balarama]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3"/> His time was close to that of [[Uraiyur Marutthuvan Dhamodharanar]], [[Kovoor Kilar]], Maadalan Madurai Kumaranar, Aavoor Moolam Kilar, [[Nakkirar I]], and Marudhanila Naganar.
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Kaari Kannanar has written 10 Sangam verses, including 5 in [[Purananuru]] (verses 57, 58, 169, 171, and 353), 1 in [[Kurunthogai]] (verse 297), 3 in [[Agananuru]] (verses 107, 123, and 285), and 1 in [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]] (verse 28).<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3"/>
